sercontent.com/a/ALm5wu3xo_XbkNq-jY-r5g5RyhPOutXdzs2aYpKPtaWH=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3", :rating=>4, :relative_time_description=>"2 weeks ago", :text=>"The soy chicken is really tender and smooth. Love the skin. Soup, bean Sprout and roasted meat is average. All the above dishes with 3 rice and 3 barley $69.50. Abit pricey for chicken rice.\n\nVerdict; will return once a while", :time=>1667625497, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"Jason Ong", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101337983538091125134/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu_jL93a3cDuKBaIRIvGZe_-LcSEo0eNTk8lGToU=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5", :rating=>4, :relative_time_description=>"7 months ago", :text=>"Even though they have been around for years, I only discovered this place a couple of years ago! But, better late than never, I guess!\nLee Fun Nam Kee specialises in soya chicken, and it shows: the chicken is usually well cooked and quite tender, and served with a generous portion of their braised sauce.\nAlong with soya chicken, they also serve char siew and roast pork. I really like the roast pork, which is tasty, tender and full of crackle! Yum!\nWe usually order some vegetable and shrimp dumpling soup as well. The bean sprouts are expertly done, just cooked and still crunchy. The shrimp dumplings are huge, and the soup is tasty. Wash it down with their homemade barley and you get a satisfying meal.\nDefinitely worth going!", :time=>1650939149, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"Richard See", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101090694756471719639/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ALm5wu16u7YQfykdfCRbNX1GakULaRMXGayL_Hnvpn9x=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5", :rating=>4, :relative_time_description=>"11 months ago", :text=>"Been here many times and one of the best place for chicken rice. Tender soy sauce chicken, flavorful fluffy rice and nice chilli with garlic. We added roast pork and char siew platter, dumplings soup and one vegetable. Yummy and will be back for more!", :time=>1640222564, :translated=>false}]}, {:editorial_summary=>{:language=>"en", :overview=>"Louisiana-inspired fast-food chain known for its spicy fried chicken, biscuits & sides."}, :name=>"Popeyes Ang Mo Kio Hub", :rating=>3.7, :reviews=>[{:author_name=>"Healin Tay", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115578908036663904498/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ALm5wu3l0-cN6-tXNbZPX7P3sNJR7uBwegDVpXtqjgy1=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4", :rating=>1, :relative_time_description=>"a year ago", :text=>"Order via GrabFood delivery. Delivery was on time with the correct Ref No number.\n\nTotal disappointment with the food order! Requested for NO Sauce for one of the 3 burgers and get 3 real plain burgers. No sauce and no vegetables!\n\nChoose to have Pepsi can but receive drink in a cup - diluted and cannot taste what drink is that!", :time=>1631769048, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"Sandra C", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105681871833096602881/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu-m-E265iz-O2-SWp-3w3v-fl8Fe8Utskl-R4lgvA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo", :rating=>1, :relative_time_description=>"a year ago", :text=>"I have purchased a promo set that has 10 pieces of chicken meat at $18.90. But I top it up with 2 buns and 1 large Rootbeer drink via online app. I ordered all these before I walked over to this branch for dine-in. To my surprise on the spot they told me no rootbeer in this branch and asked me to choose another drink which Iâ€™m fine. As I have mentioned very clear in my order that I request for Chili sauce, they told me that I can only have two small tub of chili sauce only as I purchase this promo set. After I told my partner about this, she saw that the staff gave a lot of Chili sauce sachet to other customers. We are fine if they give us two tub fully filled but too bad what we got is only a quarter of the tub filled. We confront the staff and their manager gave us another extra tub.Iâ€™m wondering why are we serve with the tub sauce just because we bought the promo set but Chili sauce sachet for normal set? Is there any differences for the profit by serving different Chili sauce size for different set? By the way this promo set is totally not worth it as they gave 2 wings, 2 drumstick, 2 chicken breast and 2 thigh. I give one star for their chicken tenderness and crunchinesses.", :time=>1634543883, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"Cindy Chua", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115133745697186961097/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu8_tQ-Ocowv_kqm2XnlocB1HpUoJIJ-tpX_G8efaw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6", :rating=>4, :relative_time_description=>"5 months ago", :text=>"Self order kiosk. Fast service. Crunchy 3 pieces chicken. I like the burger.", :time=>1655642322, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"Duminda Nirosh", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109576603969592367867/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu-h8_j_opa8qTKFfIsrBKkwaLv8abbgpdFRa5vyuA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4", :rating=>5, :relative_time_description=>"3 months ago", :text=>"Good place to eat fast food at Ang Mo Kio Hub. Quick Service.", :time=>1659146102, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"2_char", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103454518136247661704/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu9bGPWQDTOO43ruHf7rqrKhjZjjPaeQURoEkxnyJA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo", :rating=>1, :relative_time_description=>"a month ago", :text=>"Ate the food and wasnâ€™t satisfied with it but I let it slide. My relative had ordered takeout and the food was not good. Had a stomachache afterwards. There are other outlets in Singapore better than this one.\n\nEdit: Said relative is having food poisoning now from this Popeyes outlet. Since yesterday too! Seriously? Why is the standard there so subpar? I was actually shocked by the distasteful chicken sandwich I was served. I went with my friends that day and they said the same thing. As I said before, there are better outlets out there. The AMK Hub outlet isnâ€™t one of them. Upsetting.", :time=>1666188034, :translated=>false}]}, {:name=>"Casa Roma", :rating=>4.1, :reviews=>[{:author_name=>"Fion Koh", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112840814508007306480/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu-rRzsjCh5C8h_osdzkLEexoIfOHlqKS2TO6T2J=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo", :rating=>3, :relative_time_description=>"2 months ago", :text=>"Unsure itâ€™s because of the chef today or what..\n\nFish with fries lunch set was too salty (forgot to take photo of it). We werenâ€™t served any drinks or soup so I did wonder whatâ€™s the set meal about.\n\nRisotto was a little tough to chew also.\n\nThe other dish (forgot name; last photo here) was quite intriguing to me for a tryout. Average taste.\n\nOverall, it was a good lunch coz I had good company, but I probably wonâ€™t want to specifically come back for the food ðŸ˜…\n\nSpent about $68 for these 3 dishes.", :time=>1663338877, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"Audrey Low", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106024620849750975463/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ALm5wu0yi3NQv0JC9NblC8XZwJSy_5STjfDKJx6VNVsN=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo", :rating=>5, :relative_time_description=>"5 months ago", :text=>"The tiramisu is very delightful and delicious and the owner is so sweet to treat us on this wonderful dessert. Also please do order the linguine is so unique and flavourful. Please support the owner and try these unique delicious food", :time=>1654271695, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"Manoj Ramanathan", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105460206491645372350/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ALm5wu04z3De07mcdnL-mH_FNcpK0PIa7XNu4_NaXO8e=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4", :rating=>4, :relative_time_description=>"11 months ago", :text=>"Hidden inside the grandstand, a Italian restaurant that is worth the money and effort... Small place offering good Italian dishes and good service.  Outside seating available.", :time=>1639271752, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"Michele Anne Lim", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109435332808759309031/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ALm5wu2sgMGk44y8F0SSmT9V-egGmRrdHLLkKm020jH-6A=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo", :rating=>5, :relative_time_description=>"3 months ago", :text=>"We have been coming back for 20 years and the food is still as consistently authentic as when they had their Italian chef (whoâ€™s opened his own highly successful eponymous restaurant). My favourite Gnocchi Boscaiola (which is a Woodsmanâ€™s pasta sauce with caramelised onions and bacon & mushrooms) is smokey creamy and delicious, with melt in mouth gnocchi exactly as good gnocchi should be â€œsoft and delicate, with a silky-smooth textureâ€. Each member of our family has their own particular favourite: Parma ham Pizza with a perfectly done soft egg atop, Pasta Amatriciana, Arrabiata, Carbonara, Crabmeat pasta I forget the name of.", :time=>1659926194, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"Secret Sisters!!!", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102887034902684681637/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu9qXxBahfw0hjFtHtc_cQNLO5sr9qxeziUQsUJKqg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4", :rating=>5, :relative_time_description=>"6 months ago", :text=>"The food was surprisingly good. Service was good too. Unassuming authentic Italian good. Some miscommunication due to the mask while ordering but the server was so kind and offered free ice-cream to us. Highly recommend the pasta and pizza", :time=>1653307164, :translated=>false}]}, {:name=>"Peach Garden @ Thomson Plaza", :rating=>3.5, :reviews=>[{:author_name=>"jimmy lee", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110518855728692358654/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu_ufhrATfvpu6-Kg8Y3c_nscuMTK_iR9m3hhE4gfrg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5", :rating=>4, :relative_time_description=>"4 months ago", :text=>"A great place to dine with nice food and ambience. Service is good and fast too. You will need to use the Eatigo App to obtain the 50% discount to make it worthwhile. Otherwise, it is really expensive. As shown in the attached photos, the few dishes for the dinner originally cost slightly above $400. However, after the discount, the nett price of $220 is still reasonable.", :time=>1658671244, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"Taro Tan", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117655264503295909817/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu8Opaf5KnyfrPdUWDy7lBDDiMMxvsMHy_IufWZZMg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6", :rating=>3, :relative_time_description=>"4 months ago", :text=>"We enjoyed the tim sum but the variety seemed kind of a limited. Service was efficient but the meal was certainly pricey. Interesting charges for tea and wet napkins!", :time=>1657813599, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"Xin Hao", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101038177603319548234/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu9x_6WOiYD3sU-sHT_KoYi_HNWrMQJJjORqPijAEg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6", :rating=>2, :relative_time_description=>"10 months ago", :text=>"Quality of their dim sum dishes have declined. Range of dim sum options available has also shrunk - pretty disappointing. CNY price hike not justified at all even with the usual 15% discount on all Dim Sum menu. The plate of XO Carrot Cake costs $30 with only a few very small pieces of prawns and scallops. Does not taste the same as previous years at all too. Fried Rice with a few pieces of tiny abalone costs $48. All before taxes. I can understand CNY price hike but this is too unjustified. Do NOT be fooled by their 50% dim sum promotions at all. Highly recommend you visit Taste Paradise instead.\n\nStaff is overall still as efficient for higher customer turnover but please focus on improving the quality of dishes served. Perhaps better to offer an ordering sheet with clear prices of each item on the dim sum menu. Disappointing encounter.", :time=>1643118615, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"irenechong 84", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113395635442814489789/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ALm5wu3WDhPYY3mikOmwWfC6kAX2PyD48HxBIvJiw6rF=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo", :rating=>4, :relative_time_description=>"9 months ago", :text=>"Read quite a bit of bad reviews about peach garden. But for this branch, Thomson Plaza, the service is good. Staffs are friendly. The food is served in push carts and is hot and crispy. We were served immediately after we sat down. The waitresses keep pushing different Push carts to serve hot food. A lot of variety.", :time=>1645412181, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"Winnie O", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100922132461033354629/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu8Jp185DfSuXbKNYiAcWkLvYjz20pqnJmOCkzonMg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5", :rating=>4, :relative_time_description=>"8 months ago", :text=>"Iâ€™ve eaten at Peach Garden outlets elsewhere before and Iâ€™ve been impressed by the variety and quality of their food.\n\nHad the afternoon dim sum at 3 pm on a Friday at the Thomson outlet. While I enjoyed the pushcart experience and friendly aunties, the variety of dim sum was a lot less than expected.\n\nAfter several rounds of showing our table the same kinds of foods (that we ordered already), we decided to order the Peking duck. Duck was ok but could be juicier and served hot. My favorite dish was the fried wontons; fresh, crunchy and surprisingly meaty inside.\n\nService was good and staff were polite. Still prefer the Peach Garden in the CBD as my go to.", :time=>1646145530, :translated=>false}]}, {:editorial_summary=>{:language=>"en", :overview=>"Casual counter-serve chain for build-your-own sandwiches & salads, with health-conscious options."}, :name=>"SUBWAY", :rating=>4, :reviews=>[{:author_name=>"Ricka D", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108435899409616026383/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu9R4I9jH4vmLmjDqwn6jash9I2K1gf2HkWBLXdA3nk=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4", :rating=>5, :relative_time_description=>"5 months ago", :text=>"The staff at the Subway in Novena Square are really friendly and adapted to everyoneâ€™s unique requests. Even though many customers had last minute changes, they accommodated without any fuss. I especially liked the constant smile I got from this young server.\n\nThe staff is also constantly wiping down their station after making each order and I noticed they change their gloves after each order.\n\nEverything is so fresh, they bake the bread and prepare the ingredients every morning.\n\nI know Subway outlets is catered for Halal and Vegetarians.\n\nCome and try their Rendang Prawn, Chicken or Beef.", :time=>1655046600, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"Alan Tan", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109949612946343261341/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu_4pW9oph1bhUeFrf2zp8-cGvTorl258RUzlcYACg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2", :rating=>5, :relative_time_description=>"5 months ago", :text=>"Iâ€™m a big fan of Subway for the healthy, fresh and tasty sandwiches. Been to quite a few stores around Singapore and this newly-renovated one at Novena Square is absolutely the best of the lot.  Bright, spacious, well laid-out and with piped music to boot, this outlet had the typical Subway menu with freshest of vegetables! There was also seating just outside of the store which looked into the bustling atrium of the mall.\n\nAlso chanced upon the owner, a lovely and gracious lady behind the cashier. Friendly service and a clean environment made it such an expectedly pleasant sandwich lunch!", :time=>1654075329, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"Eunjung Lee", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/118187540839317356163/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ALm5wu0HT0uLqUYcru4JkWVINduRYJLlCe-QH5TuHIW4eh8=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo", :rating=>1, :relative_time_description=>"4 months ago", :text=>"Don't want to come anymore.\nReally ridiculous.\nI didn't eat anything.before take a pic\nThis vege so precious right?\nThat's why, they don't want to give me more. This is $8.1 salad.\nThey don't use Spoon no accurate amount.  Just person using hand little bit.\nThe malay lady said already extra a lot. If u want to more extra charge. I want to call incharge but no time, and don't want to wasting my time and energy to them.\n\nThe last pic is other branch no extra charge.  Same price. This is obvious different", :time=>1658469727, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"murali chandran", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106887980565790652255/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu-9M8z9YNfZvKR04VtgGwaWme2GsAtcqPUrgDTm4go=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo", :rating=>5, :relative_time_description=>"5 months ago", :text=>"What a fantastic experience at this store. The staff were so friendly in explaining the differences in the menu compared to the US stores. Being a high maintenance eater, I wanted my beef rendang just right. They set it up just right.... No rubber l wonder this is a popular dining option for lunch and dinner.", :time=>1655024344, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"shu yuan", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108683846568401465760/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ALm5wu2xsBm0iOoAhkT0cd6scGPsNSUN5otWsR_Q7v8W=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo", :rating=>1, :relative_time_description=>"a month ago", :text=>"The subway here gives very less sauce all the time , the sandwich always ended up to be too dry. Therefore today i ask for more sauce once, the Indian lady at the sauce section rolled here eyes on me before putting in more sauce. During payment time the malay lady at the cashier area was so rude, i ordered a bottle of water for my meal, and she jus pointed out that the water is at the outside the counter, i said okay ill take it myself later then, she follow by \"i need to put it in now\" thats all. Im supposed to figured out myself that she want me to take the bottle of water for her so she can put in the bag for me...", :time=>1666330320, :translated=>false}]}, {:name=>"Fusion Bistro", :rating=>4.5, :reviews=>[{:author_name=>"Khai Rizal", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106011534035514299585/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleuser