iews=>[{:author_name=>"Adrian Chan", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109957919811943890317/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu99dkGu9V0gBYiez1tULt3NIyUzL-ND6XcukqhylQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5", :rating=>5, :relative_time_description=>"11 months ago", :text=>"Nice and cosy cafe with very friendly staff. We tried their Egg's Benedict and Egg's Royal's (smoked salmon) and it was good - bread was nicely toasted and easy to cut through. Price is typical cafe price but it is definitely worth it for the food and ambience.", :time=>1640491657, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"Gabriel Quek (GabrielQ)", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111029600621744254559/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ALm5wu03rZIfaxWGCLGgxf1GOnsdD1z_9u2MO9yJKalX=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4", :rating=>3, :relative_time_description=>"8 months ago", :text=>"The place was busy on a Sunday morning. Had the weekly lunch set, went for the mushroom soup, eggs benedict, and a hot latte.\n\nFrankly, my expectations were high as the smells from the bakery was amazing. And coupled with the fact that it was highly recommended by a friend, I honestly expected more.\n\nThe eggs benedict was ordinary and one dimensional, the mushroom soup was way too watery and diluted tasting, and the coffee was thoroughly ordinary (doesn't compete with most 3rd wave cafes).\n\nI'll be back to give the baked goods a try. But till then, this was a 3 star experience.", :time=>1647232832, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"WPin P", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117893368337848889092/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu-tsICRIiOtc7V7MrAKc0-Rqg5CHgFTRWi7M7YWPA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3", :rating=>5, :relative_time_description=>"6 months ago", :text=>"Choupinette is a fav breakfast-brunch haunt for many, with their freshly baked breads & French menu.\nSurprised (and really glad) that they have recently extended their operating hours to include dinner service.\nGood & honest French fares with yummy tarts for dessert ðŸ˜‹ good wine selections â€¦ with the occasional surprise craft beer on tap ðŸ‘ðŸ¼\nDo enquire about their off menu specials ðŸ˜‰", :time=>1652600702, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"Wesker Ling", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103716517052524321701/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu-MqIu06VXqjuypXyZj3l5Dir8sDSjZ3ocWQLeGUg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3", :rating=>5, :relative_time_description=>"10 months ago", :text=>"\"Probably the Best croissants in Town!!\" ^^\n\nI was introduced to Choupinette by a friend. She told me that they have the best croissant in town, the butter & ingredients was from French. So as a croissant lover, I definitely must visit!!\n\nIt turn out the foods were really delicious, croissant with great butter smell. (We had 6 more croissants take away after that hehe XD).  Managed to tried their Eggs Benedict too, the made their own bread (very crispy), & marinated their own ham (taste just nice not too salty). Super Duper Good.!!!!\n\nIf you planned to come here for croissant or any other breads, please visit earlier as 8am or make reservation. It sold fast, because they baked fresh daily. ^^\n\nWe were blessed to be taken care by both Force (lady) & Jason, they were very professional & humor! Super friendly! ^^ LOL\nIf you are going there for first time, please feel free to seek their help with recommendation, and make your own decision.", :time=>1642777668, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"L Y", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116804450051508415316/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ALm5wu2MRH-merJQUoecEurI_t1nWEt9R6Vfn9CfiHKV=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4", :rating=>5, :relative_time_description=>"8 months ago", :text=>"We came for a late lunch on a weekday and it was not crowded. I suspect it's not that the food is no good, but the competition is very stiff for a casual meal in this vicinity. Choupinette is quaint little bistro serving hearty french food, and one must be prepared to dish out about $30 per pax for a casual meal.\n\nWe had the Croque Monsieur and Egg Benedict. Both are good quality and very substantial casual meals. Our cheerful server,  Wan persuaded us to get the off-menu Cajun Fries. It was very crispy and yummy.\n\nWe'd be back again to try their famous croissants.", :time=>1646834185, :translated=>false}]}, {:name=>"My Little Spanish Place (Bukit Timah)", :rating=>4.3, :reviews=>[{:author_name=>"Luvena K", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104734218790964741467/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ALm5wu0vuxaZWiaFRkJpoOLFdpHkoSKRn9yxikL7kc0L=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo", :rating=>4, :relative_time_description=>"2 weeks ago", :text=>"This neighborhood gem has good food, service and warm atmosphere with greeted into red brick wall interior on one side and wine bottle display on the other.\n\nRecommend the Ribeye for main. The beef tender and juicy enough, paired with the flavorful suace and potato puree.\n\nIt's a midweek and the tables are mostly occupied, we glad we came a little early that they could accommodate us without reservation.\n\nServer was great and food came out pretty quick considering the busy kitchen.\n\nWith our hearty big meal, we walked out of this restaurant satisfied and planning to return.", :time=>1667392092, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"Jamie W", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111972747533251569870/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_