n, I didnâ€™t forget to also order it here. To be honest, they have more options than some restaurants that we went in Spain lol. Love their food, especially the Paella. And love the casual / cozy vibe of the restaurant as well.", :time=>1642229079, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"jianhao lee", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107431589322877158256/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu9vndaX2fkHpGTW16trZpZvblLWW5xUdX-dK5PP7OQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5", :rating=>5, :relative_time_description=>"10 months ago", :text=>"First time trying this place. Reservation should always be made before coming. It is always full. Came on a Saturday afternoon and is crowded. Ordered 3 tapas + 1 main = SGD 114. It is worth the price. My family all agreed that the food are delicious. The place is renovated nicely. Parking will be an issue during peak hours. Customer service is good too. This is a place i will be back again!", :time=>1642761779, :translated=>false}]}, {:editorial_summary=>{:language=>"en", :overview=>"Airy, light-filled restaurant with a casual vibe offering hearty global standards & outdoor seating."}, :name=>"Canopy Bishan", :rating=>4, :reviews=>[{:author_name=>"William Lou", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115969486686664081306/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu9viAQfpfMyNITiDO6HnGfbmGAxdVjub_8-gISL=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba8", :rating=>5, :relative_time_description=>"2 months ago", :text=>"Went for breakfast here ðŸ³ as early as 9am in the morning when they just opened. The air con was cold and no other customer yet.\n\nI loved the Egg Benedict, came with 2 eggs ðŸ¥š with hams ðŸ¥“ and bread ðŸž, mushroom ðŸ„ and leafs ðŸŒ¿. I really enjoyed the breakfast with coffee here. The truffle fries ðŸŸ were also good with their tartar sauce.\n\nLovely environment to enjoy cafe with indoor and outdoor seating.\n\nPets are allowed here but outdoor seating only.", :time=>1663040650, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"Bibiy's Day", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108318910760693495809/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu9f1aj-mVRJQMfFa3-TDTBysgn9Szjra1VRu_pLiQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5", :rating=>5, :relative_time_description=>"8 months ago", :text=>"Dog friendly cafe at Bishan Park with indoor and outdoor area. Both area has nice ambience. We came after scooting around Bishan. Food comes with beautiful plating with great taste. Juicy lamb rack! It might be for tasting only if you have a big appetite. Great place for coffee time and chit chat with your beloved family or best friend. Coffee and dessert were good too.", :time=>1647929886, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"Lynn Morabe", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111150362978240358590/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu97cayvGg4iqXj61xCsEVhdCF1R1u0-u9efHQUI=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4", :rating=>4, :relative_time_description=>"3 months ago", :text=>"Had dinner here on National Day with my kids and dog. Made a reservation and was seated outdoors. Price is not cheap but food, portions and service are good. Chili crab pasta was a long wait. We didn't like the lemonade. Everything else we ordered were yummy :) The place is within Bishan park and close to a dog park.", :time=>1660840920, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"PY", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101942741229132110086/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ALm5wu0VYykwblEY_HUtCyX7qAIIzWNQ-bIQivUSRbSw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4", :rating=>4, :relative_time_description=>"2 months ago", :text=>"We chose to have weekend lunch here due to proximity to Bishan park. We were seated outdoors as indoors was fully reserved.\nThe lush greenery is beautiful! We had a walk and play at the nearby playground after lunch.\nFood wise was good but tad pricey.", :time=>1661600546, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"Lazy Houzz", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110354872173947959053/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu8B-GRcleoYSDMxda8__p5H57-vnSevhr4PMzit=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3", :rating=>5, :relative_time_description=>"10 months ago", :text=>"Food portion definitely not for big eater. Nice food presentation but a bit long waiting. It has indoor and outdoor. Outdoor is mainly for those who bring doggy. Tables are a bit crowded due to limited space. Overall the atmosphere and the location in the park still make this cafe busy.", :time=>1641710856, :translated=>false}]}, {:name=>"Peperoni Pizzeria @ Greenwood", :rating=>4.4, :reviews=>[{:author_name=>"Jimmy Liaw", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109624032060261463105/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu-m4CenHoEb7m-qMK4sqlBzgTMy0Lyp49YX_2rS-Oc=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5", :rating=>5, :relative_time_description=>"a month ago", :text=>"Always a nice dining experience at Peperoni. V popular so be sure to make reservations.\n\nSlightly tweaked menu on last visit. Ordered the newly added pesto pasta. Not bad, but had better. A little bland, and no pine nuts seen.\n\nCarbonara is excellent as usual. So is their pizza", :time=>1666242346, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"Rachel Luyi", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105345832861069223691/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu-SfrMKlRJ3Vu2xPV2XZnvM8D56g0n2yWQZ74b8ew=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5", :rating=>4, :relative_time_description=>"11 months ago", :text=>"Pizza is thin and crust is crispy but best of all, you can enjoy 2 different flavours in 1 pizza! Best of both worlds.\n\nFood was tasty and pasta was well cooked. May return if I'm in the area.", :time=>1640176191, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"Joyce Lim", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114306834103372851451/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu_9yQeJOkh5BEhndF4-O6XKYCbLO2oPADKHFojiWg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5", :rating=>4, :relative_time_description=>"3 months ago", :text=>"Friendly and great customer service, good ambience, can get quite loud indoors due to acoustics. Minus one star as they don't serve water. Food was great in general but carne part of xxl was way too salty n pesto tasted minty which was weird. Nevertheless great place for a noisy large group gathering. Toilet clean n adequate. Parking can be tough as it's first come first serve limited street side n free.", :time=>1660313707, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"Alicia Lee", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110152137873405295467/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu_KkGb2snBc1HSG5728ldUhFtLdpKpMj3Xhoj6gXfQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5", :rating=>5, :relative_time_description=>"a year ago", :text=>"Staff is very attentive here and the food is served fast! Ordered the half half XXL pizza and it can feed up to 5. The Parma ham pizza is good! The seafood one is average. A bit fishy. Overall still love the taste of all the food. Chicken wings are good! Calamari is quite average too. Dining area is very spacious", :time=>1630893119, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"I Kuan", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109450580898345386769/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu-zxoSBaost5QUkaobtyKQT_9RqIJicljg2Y-NzVDQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3", :rating=>5, :relative_time_description=>"3 months ago", :text=>"Friendly staff, cosy and charming atmosphere that has warmly welcomed patrons since early 2000s. Great for families! Al fresco dining options out front as well as in the back. Pizzas are nice and thin crusted, and come in 3 sizes - 9\", 12\", 21\" XXL. I've seen an older couple devour a whole XXL pizza over dinner before! The happy hour drinks are pretty good value for money.\n\n[Update] We tried the XXL and managed to devour it between 2 adults and 1 hungry, growing tween! Fantastic value!", :time=>1661014000, :translated=>false}]}, {:editorial_summary=>{:language=>"en", :overview=>"Restaurant chain known for its buckets of fried chicken, plus wings & sides."}, :name=>"KFC", :rating=>3.8, :reviews=>[{:author_name=>"Jorban Morandoo", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103806214590406329633/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ALm5wu2EUuxNp4ldZZh-r7HKh9rTqBqii8Q_pNFT2s2d=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo", :rating=>1, :relative_time_description=>"6 months ago", :text=>"The quality of the food at this outlet has been extremely poor, for as long as I can remember. These are the tenders. This is also the curry rice box. BARELY ANY CURRY. Disappointing. Do not recommend people to come here. The PizzaHut RIGHT BESIDE has much better service and quality of food.", :time=>1651230327, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"Wan Wen Chew", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115909486226864722566/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ALm5wu3iJIS9qzTs1w8Wdnho8yQ13r1oyb5_FVkqMqq2=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo", :rating=>1, :relative_time_description=>"4 months ago", :text=>"Worse kfc outlet ever. Service was poor. Waited for almost 1 hr for our food. You call this fast food? Seriously? Went over to ask how long more do i have to wait. The staff never even apologise but just shut me off saying many people today. From what i see, the restaurant was not even fully filled. The staffs are taking their time to prepare the food which is causing the high demand.\nOverall really super poor service!", :time=>1658492986, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"Moony Chant", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114712059839882027448/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu8PqoaX0Ghy0tzFYMq4BlKSZ16Loh5JBbc7ob2Q3A=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3", :rating=>4, :relative_time_description=>"2 months ago", :text=>"Nice & quiet location. Service is fast too.", :time=>1662989247, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"Sheena Lim", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112497410669722888696/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu826caAboTDzldjy_yvbY_sKi-6WJSg8gmR1RyWZA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3", :rating=>1, :relative_time_description=>"a month ago", :text=>"If I can put zero stars I wld .. Place here doesn't have screen tht shows our q number . I appreciate your staff calling our numbers fearing we dint get our food in time . But pls lah if call twice n infront is empty means we sitting behind what there's not a need for tht impatient tone of calling for the third time or in fact shouting for the number .. Pls educate your staff to call for number not shout number in an unhappy tone if we dun react fast enuf . It's ok if I'm an adult what if is an elderly leh ? Have you ever thot of it before ?", :time=>1664435447, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"Faith Child", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108151252889443314104/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ALm5wu10VRchkZ_-M1bZZBHPz2cWA58IoMZdC1P6daAX=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2", :rating=>1, :relative_time_description=>"2 weeks ago", :text=>"Spit on it...chicken size shrink..ordered set don't even bother to give cup.. and also no spoon given ..SVC never change for the past 3 years since I visited... This KFC outlet here is famous for their missing item trend..do check Ur take away before leaving or the meal will spoil your entire day...", :time=>1667889601, :translated=>false}]}, {:editorial_summary=>{:language=>"en", :overview=>"Basic, popular hawker stall doling out nasi lemak, fried chicken wings & other familiar Asian eats."}, :name=>"Selera Rasa Nasi Lemak", :rating=>3.9, :reviews=>[{:author_name=>"Michael Esesjay", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105215085834173868326/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu9mK3T2l7M0LDKPCiMmBLGNuFuSlNHHQvRZjQYTfA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4", :rating=>4, :relative_time_description=>"a month ago", :text=>"This is a very late review. I was looking into my phone's gallery and came across the photos I took when I went cycling 13 km just to get to their place to try their NASI LEMAK.  Damn It's been 3 years already.  One of the best Nasi Lemak I've tried. Fragrant rice, crispy chicken and a flavourful sambal. Lucky that when I visited the place there was not much queue. I will definitely come back once I passed by the area.", :time=>1666312614, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"Live2nJOY", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117765677281458957067/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu9X5YpY8QMPlaMngze-rQzbffYbeXi-jaAhJ174=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5", :rating=>4, :relative_time_description=>"6 months ago", :text=>"Very fragrant and delicious nasi Lemak, fish and chicken wing were flavorful and yummy. Stall bro was also very friendly!!! @live2njoy", :time=>1652002075, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"Matthew Lee", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109397825257995094119/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ALm5wu2Rp_2AIp9dN8NgCmzHOlEft2RUDUiPXtjlr9Qt=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6", :rating=>3, :relative_time_description=>"8 months ago", :text=>"The queue wasn't really long but the waiting time was. I see the people in the queue are ordering like 1-2 plates and the turnaround time was quite fast, but they were preparing all the big pre orders which was like for the whole kampong in between customers causing the queue not to move for some time.\nFood wise, I would say it's better than average but not really to consider fantastic. The only thing I liked was the bismati rice and the sweet-and-not-so-spicy chili. The other items on the list were pretty normal.\nMenu wise quite fixed, and they don't really have the flexibility to add extra stuff. I don't really blame them as it might just jam up the queue, and I wished they have egg!", :time=>1648390547, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"Kallen Tu", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115474890042460489365/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu9VwzJ5q1YQXddx3aw5Y2uFRmhvLHGRYGafHIlHbA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6", :rating=>5, :relative_time_description=>"5 months ago", :text=>"B and G sets were gone by the time we got there around noon. The portion was good and the otak was pretty good. I had a royal flush.\nWait didn't take too long but there usually is a line.", :time=>1654466091, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"Alan Tang", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/118416171152567325758/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu8ctdcXSFJeHpryROBOC9f54WeHxMA0it56tKl2=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4", :rating=>4, :relative_time_description=>"5 months ago", :text=>"One of the better Nasi Lemak place we like. Unfortunately, the â€œikan kuningâ€ was sold out even at 10am. The friendly Stall holder â€œDaveâ€ said there was no fish for last two days and when the fish was available this morning, it was sold very quickly.\n\nWe had to settle for Set C which was the fried chicken wing with ikan bilis/peanut mix, fried egg and two slices of cucumber.\n\nIt was good as we like their basmati rice, of course with their special Sambal Chilli.", :time=>1655965052, :translated=>false}]}, {:name=>"Casuarina Curry (Thomson)", :rating=>3.8, :reviews=>[{:author_name=>"Grace Lee", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114868807802053749557/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ALm5wu1lj8M4pGBURe5sZgdaA3BizJFFP1N2XPI9MmPU=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5", :rating=>4, :relative_time_description=>"a month ago", :text=>"Large dining area, clean. Finding a parking lot can be a challenge. Limited nos. Good variety of curries. Lamb shank curry was good. Murtabak stood out for me, mutton and gravy flavourful. Mango lassi could have less ice. Overall a satisfying dinner. I would have preferred if all the veggies were more warm than cold.", :time=>1666105260, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"Jason Ong", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101337983538091125134/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu_jL93a3cDuKBaIRIvGZe_-LcSEo0eNTk8lGToU=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5", :rating=>4, :relative_time_description=>"5 months ago", :text=>"Great place for prata. The Tissue Prata was really thin and crispy. They serve crispy type prata. The egg onion prata is delicious too.\nWe were first given chicken curry, and when we asked for a refill, were served fish curry. Both were flavourful and yummy.\nIt gets crowded, and there's not a lot of parking available. Go during off peak hours or travel by public transport.", :time=>1655808476, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"Rahul Bhade", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116230312837172130344/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu9Ne-qTTAQ1PpGvaEx9Zg-xj74kUSY7ibs6yjwmQoo=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5", :rating=>2, :relative_time_description=>"3 weeks ago", :text=>"Came here after a hike at MacRitchie Reservoir..\nOrdering is an irritating and cumbersome experience.\nThe uncle was on the phone and never bothered to take the order and then went away to do something..came back again and was on the phone again but luckily decided to oblige and take the order.\nFood came quickly, but was lukewarm.\nThe prata had some chemical sort of smell but was crisp.\nFish curry sauce that came alongside had a good creamy dipping texture.\nSpecial mention to the Mysore mutton which was tender and evenly spiced.\nWonâ€™t specifically come here..better ones around.", :time=>1666834574, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"Nivi Prabhu", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116708965627849447887/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu8TaFM3ntyOj4mhOOJqInbiDDzJWExfHXaFwdxEo1k=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5", :rating=>4, :relative_time_description=>"7 months ago", :text=>"The first I came here, I could not get in as it was full and waiting time was waay too long for my hangry self. This time, I came on a weekday evening. At 8pm the place was half full giving me ample space choices. I chose to sit out. The food was good, not great but the prata was the star of the show. I had ordered chicken masala, which is a chefs recommendation but I did not like it that much. The mutton dishes and the plain gravy that came with the prata was nice!", :time=>1648645429, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"Gabi Quek", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112281547460445739231/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu_QJelB7Yy11D480ndT0-NVwuJtI_5A8kI20NVPJw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2", :rating=>4, :relative_time_description=>"in the last week", :text=>"First time back after a few years. Now the prata comes pre cooked which isnt too great. Stand out dishes were the lamb shank ala carte and the spinach and lentil curry. Extremely flavourful and satisfying", :time=>1668749037, :translated=>false}]}, {:name=>"Founder Bak Kut Teh", :rating=>4, :reviews=>[{:author_name=>"Anna Marie Alde", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/118367148317040157660/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ALm5wu0URn9yVqVb2H7GA-i_Wc-M-KfOidFR5bo7CA9T=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5", :rating=>5, :relative_time_description=>"9 months ago", :text=>"Our go-to comfort food especially on a cold & rainy night ... tender pork ribs in a bowl of hot, savory, peppery, garlicky broth really hits the spot. Must go with their crispy you tiao. Love their braised pork trotters and salted vegetables, too. ðŸ˜‹ðŸ˜‹ðŸ˜‹", :time=>1644152507, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"Jason Ong", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101337983538091125134/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu_jL93a3cDuKBaIRIvGZe_-LcSEo0eNTk8lGToU=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5", :rating=>4, :relative_time_description=>"3 months ago", :text=>"There were several stalls offering BKT in Balestier back in the 90s. And this was one of them. I remember that even then, there were already photos of guests with the owner being put up on the walls. Being near to MediaCorp (which was just a few minutes away then), the shop used to draw many artistes who were filming there.\nUnlike many others, the BKT here is served in rather large bowls, like those I used to have as a kid. The pepper soup has a nice kick, not overpowering. The sliced pork was tender and juicy, but the regular pork ribs were tough and chewy. The Tang O vegetables were generously portioned.\nWhile this humble shop may have fallen out of fashion with the masses, it's still worth visiting. Park along one of the side roads and walk there. You can see the character of the area which is different from most housing estates.", :time=>1660176225, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"Saifu Angto", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101827544393066516766/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu-Y9jG5qZ90IZ_BrYm0aDyuTBkpSlRgHxsjsvpdnlM=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6", :rating=>4, :relative_time_description=>"6 months ago", :text=>"This is one of the several Bak Kut Teh place in the area (Balestier and Rangoon Road).  Tried it for the first time, and was debating between this and Loy Kee chicken rice place across the street.\n\nOrdered the Founder Bak Kut Teh, lettuce stir fry, braised peanut and salted vegetable.  They gave use second bowl of soup from the get go, and the ribs were good and soft.  The salted vegetable was nice, not too sour.  The braised peanut is nice and soft, large size, but it's a bit bland.  The soup is good, less peppery compared to Song Fa.\n\nOverall is good.  Song Fa soup is more peppery, comparable to Ng Ah Sio on Rangoon Rd.", :time=>1653138567, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"Ivan Teh", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114332345573544911646/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu-1rmdjnZD8KAET1jssmMrooxfSGUhESUjLtU0XtQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6", :rating=>5, :relative_time_description=>"9 months ago", :text=>"Bak Kut Teh (SGD $18) @ Founder Bak Kut Teh.\n.\nOn the spectrum of BKT, you have the potent peppery broth on one end, and the robust herbal broth on the other.\n.\nSince 1978, the version here is unique for occupying the middle, blending both savoury peppery and herbal sweet flavours, an enticing medley.\n.\nThe premium pork ribs are large and meaty, with tender pork that comes off the bone easily, having a savoury herbal sweet flavour from the broth.\n.\nThe pickled salted mustard greens have a medium vegetal salty sweet flavour with a soft crunch, while the braised egg has a bold soy sauce gravy that is best paired with white rice.", :time=>1644123094, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"Jenny Nguyen", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115537761649320194511/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu-zDzRCePZcZCUw_cTPx3gaCWZFfwn-0Z1CeWAutg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo", :rating=>5, :relative_time_description=>"4 months ago", :text=>"Fast service, their price is ~20% higher than other places but it's reasonable cuz they use only fresh pork to cook. I know this because my hubby is a food supplier. The ribs are addictive.", :time=>1657496668, :translated=>false}]}, {:name=>"Brazil Churrasco", :rating=>4.6, :reviews=>[{:author_name=>"Randy Ngatimin", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107076346774947547605/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu-i-QeGRQVjqnpEAsstrkH50xbqWsob8XxxZbhXNQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6", :rating=>4, :relative_time_description=>"9 months ago", :text=>"Great experience in this restaurant!\nWaiters were attentive and fast; quite a big selection of meat choices; meat quality were generally good; Ham is surprisingly good as I like the smokey and BBQ-y flavour infused into it; try the pineapple as it helps to balance out on overeating of the meat!", :time=>1644797345, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"WendyCC", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111849994934797387856/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu8bcHFBwJNM7YLvD1bl9kWAhaIbSezQZav51E0LTQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5", :rating=>5, :relative_time_description=>"4 months ago", :text=>"We love this place. We dine here nearly once every other month. They have a good variety of meats and the beef were especially good. Well flavoured and nicely grilled. Itâ€™s a fun place to enjoy meats with a twist and have some fun while dining. They also have other meats like chicken, fish etc but their main dish is beef. They also have a buffet counter for salads and sides which u can help yourself to now that the restrictions have been lifted. Other than the grilled meats, the grilled pineapple, crispy kale, fried quinoa and frijoles are a must try. U can also BYOB there at a corkage charge of $30. If you BYOB, a weekend dinner for two will cost about $195", :time=>1658471012, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"jajaish", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106488746205330927683/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu_guTMeTdLLVw1rRzdIWxI6sgjDvwYWl59d-oavNSs=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5", :rating=>4, :relative_time_description=>"12 months ago", :text=>"Overall not bad. Not amazing. But definite value for money. At first the meats were a bit on the medium well done side, but after ask, the medium rare meats were nice. Ask for salt and pepper on the side to season more properly. Wine corkage was $30.", :time=>1637658592, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"Wendy Hoe", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/118015064178224679304/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ALm5wu04AZIBNKl28PhZItZBtzk5BzheeU_m8EEgtGcs=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5", :rating=>5, :relative_time_description=>"6 months ago", :text=>"The staff were friendly, service was top notch & the ambience was cozy.\nThe food & dessert were amazing.\nIf you are a meat person, it's a must to try.", :time=>1653267428, :translated=>false}, {:author_name=>"Annie Liu", :author_url=>"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101897397769903518974/reviews", :language=>"en", :original_language=>"en", :profile_photo_url=>"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu9ntkgebBeiw-2yJpONh68hHTlRpZgQ0q13KnthIg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3", :rating=>5, :relative_time_description=>"a month ago", :text=>"This has been my favourite Brazilian restaurant since more than 10 years ago. Still amazing as usual.\n\nBesides all the amazing meat spread,  I actually came for the banana fritters and cheese bread. Didn't count how many were down this time but definitely went for a few rounds. ðŸ˜…ðŸ˜‚\n\nThe bbq caramelised pineapple also a unique thing here which you should try if you like sweet stuff. Still worth to try if you are not.ðŸ˜\n\nYou can also try the Brazilian all time favourite soda - Guarana.\n\nI love today's pumpkin soup served in a very cute tiny tea cup, makes drinking soup in a pretty fun way.", :time=>1665012116, :translated=>false}]}]
